# Tenancy — <%= appName %>

Strategy: **<%= tenancyMode %>**

Multi-tenant context via AsyncLocalStorage and request header resolution.

## Modes

| Mode | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `single-db` | Shared database; filter rows by tenant id in application code |
| `schema-per-tenant` | PostgreSQL schema per tenant (`tenant_<id>`) |
| `db-per-tenant` | Dedicated `DATABASE_URL_<TENANT>` env var per tenant |

## Environment

```env
TENANT_HEADER=x-tenant-id
DEFAULT_TENANT=default
<% if (tenancyMode === 'schema-per-tenant') { %>
TENANT_SCHEMA_PREFIX=tenant_
<% } else if (tenancyMode === 'db-per-tenant') { %>
DATABASE_URL_ACME=postgresql://...
DATABASE_URL_GLOBEX=postgresql://...
<% } %>
```

## Usage

```typescript
import { registerTenancyMiddleware, getTenantId<% if (tenancyMode === 'schema-per-tenant') { %>, getTenantSchema<% } else if (tenancyMode === 'db-per-tenant') { %>, getTenantDatabaseUrl<% } %> } from './src/platform/tenancy/index.js';

await registerTenancyMiddleware(app);
const tenant = getTenantId();
<% if (tenancyMode === 'schema-per-tenant') { %>
const schema = getTenantSchema();
<% } else if (tenancyMode === 'db-per-tenant') { %>
const databaseUrl = getTenantDatabaseUrl();
<% } %>
```

Run `my add tenancy --mode <%= tenancyMode %>` to regenerate this module.
